The paper discusses a new framework for feature construction, which is a common topic in machine learning (ML) and falls under the category of supervised learning. The paper also mentions the use of outlier detection and discriminative pattern mining, which are techniques commonly used in ML for data preprocessing and feature engineering. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.DM (Data Mining), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.CL (Computation and Language) as these sub-categories are closely related to the topic of the paper.
